        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 22 at 3:27PM CDT until August 22 at 4:15PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>SVRBRO

The National Weather Service in Brownsville has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Central Kenedy County in Deep South Texas...

* Until 415 PM CDT.

* At 327 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Armstrong,
and is nearly stationary.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Armstrong, Kenedy County Wind Farms, and Armstrong Ranch Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
